# Security & privacy

- **Never commit secrets.** Use `.env` (git-ignored) locally and a secret manager in prod.
  `.env.example` documents keys with placeholder values only.
- **Minimize PII.** Especially for election observers / tipsters: collect the minimum, hash
  identifiers, encrypt at rest, restrict access. Do not repeat the government portal's data-leak
  failure.
- **SSRF guards** on any endpoint that fetches a user-supplied URL (block localhost/link-local/
  file:; validate scheme+host). See PeaDF `extract-content` blocked-host pattern.
- **Respect law/ToS** when fetching. Closed/paywalled sources go through the FOI/legal workstream,
  not brute-force scraping.
- **Least privilege** for DB/storage credentials; separate read vs write roles for the public API.
- **Lawful & nonpartisan.** No evasion/anonymity tooling; no partisan targeting. Openness is the
  security model.
